title: Rodgers a free agent for 1st time as Jets cut QB
description: The Jets officially released Aaron Rodgers on Wednesday, making him a free agent for the first time in his career.
author: Rich Cimini

title: Sources: LeBron returns to L.A. for treatment
description: Lakers star LeBron James has returned to Los Angeles, per medical recommendation, as he continues to progress well from a groin strain he suffered against the Boston Celtics on Saturday, league sources told ESPN.
author: Dave McMenamin

title: The double-kick penalty that cost Atletico Madrid in shootout
description: Julian Alvarez's penalty in the shootout between Atletico Madrid and Real Madrid is ruled out after he slips and is deemed to have hit the ball twice in one movement.

title: Will PSG tie provide Champions League redemption for Emery?
description: Aston Villa manager Unai Emery will get a shot at redemption for the lowest point of his stellar European career when he faces former club Paris St-Germain in the Champions League quarter-final.

title: NFL free agency grades: Guess who is getting an A?
description: Between a few big trades and a flurry of overall activity, aggressive teams improved. But some teams took hits with players leaving.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: Tiger Woods out indefinitely after undergoing surgery for ruptured Achilles, will miss the Masters
description: Tiger Woods underwent surgery to repair his ruptured Achilles on Tuesday.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: Why was Alvarez's shoot-out pen vs Real ruled out - and should it have been?
description: Julian Alvarez's spot kick was controversially ruled out in Atletico Madrid's shoot-out defeat to Real Madrid in the Champions League - but why was it disallowed, and did the forward even break the rules at all?

title: Van Dijk has 'no idea' if he will extend Liverpool stay
description: Virgil van Dijk says talks with Liverpool over a new deal are "not on hold" but he still has "no idea" what will happen in the summer, when his contract is set to expire.
